column5: Hey guys,  Found this posted on a board down here. The guy said it was pulled outta Nippising.    Any of you guys seen pics of this?   FHR
yes it is two pikes with one head stuck inside the gill flap of another.
That been around for 5 years at least.
I believe hammerhandle pike is checking out the gills of respectable pike
Thanks, thought the water in Nip. might be going wacky or something. :/  FHR

FishHeadRick has been conspicuous by his absence lately.  Dude had his photo published in OOD with a nice 35 in pike with the CN tower in the background, and he posted that photo first, here on OFC.  Hope all is well with Mr DLC.
Had me going for a minute until I noticed one pike is on its side  Now rick give us one of your ocean reports
Stumbled on this one yesterday. Nice looking dogfish...
Kinda like this catfish    Joey  p.s.  doesn't the guy with the dogfish look suspiciously like our very own Reefhawg/Adam
